      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmarked against at least one canonical rotating-flow problem with published analytical or highly-resolved reference solution.",
      "rationale": "Fluent rotating-frame solver verified against Taylor-Couette flow benchmark (Re = 1200). Computed velocity profiles agree with analytical solution to within 0.4% at all radial stations. Benchmark case archived alongside production simulation inputs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or GCI analysis on at least three mesh levels; GCI on QOI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (3.1M, 7.8M, 18.4M hexahedral cells). Grid Convergence Index on relative hemolysis index: 2.7% on fine-to-medium pair, 3.9% on medium-to-coarse pair. Asymptotic range confirmed (GCI ratio 0.97). Production mesh is the 7.8M-cell medium grid, balancing accuracy and throughput for the 5-operating-point design space."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) documented and matched in simulation to within stated measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Bench test conditions documented per ASTM F1841. Flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min, rotational speed to ±10 RPM, temperature to ±0.5°C. Simulation inlet BCs set to measured mean values; fluid properties assigned at measured temperature. Measurement uncertainty propagated into UQ analysis using Monte Carlo sampling across 2000 realisations, with aggregate output uncertainty reported as ±9.1% on RHI. A screening sensitivity study is discussed in the UQ report to indicate which parameters contribute most to output variance, though structured ranking results are embedded within the narrative rather than as a separate linked artefact."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric (e.g., NRMSE or validation uncertainty) computed for primary QOI across all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index compared at all 5 operating points. Validation metric U_val computed per ASME V&V 20. Model prediction interval overlaps experimental measurement interval at all points. Maximum discrepancy 8.6% at 4500 RPM / 4 L/min, within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty band."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOI directly maps to the clinical decision metric (RH index) used in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "The primary QOI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and its relative form (RHI). These quantities are the accepted regulatory metrics for CPB device hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance and ISO 10993-4. The model outputs RHI at each operating point, directly supporting the RH < 1 acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same pump geometry, blood analog fluid, and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump geometry using porcine blood at 37°C across the 5 flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Operating conditions span the intended clinical envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–5000 RPM). No extrapolation beyond validated envelope required for the submission operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated by residual reduction of at least 4 orders of magnitude and stabilisation of QOI monitor.",
      "rationale": "All steady-state solutions converged to residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum. RHI monitor stabilised to within 0.1% over the final 500 iterations. Convergence plots archived for each of the 5 operating points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 when model is operated by trained simulation engineers under institutional review.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Simulation operated by PhD-level engineers with >5 years CFD experience. Institutional peer-review checklist completed prior to submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selected based on literature evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices; model form uncertainty acknowledged.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for centrifugal blood pumps (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012). Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied; model form uncertainty estimated at ±15% on absolute NIH based on inter-model comparison in literature. Model form uncertainty incorporated into total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties, geometric tolerances, and boundary condition distributions documented with sources and assigned uncertainty ranges.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity assigned Newtonian approximation at 37°C (3.5 mPa·s ±8%) based on ISO 10993-4 reference fluid. Pump geometry from manufacturer CAD with dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm. Inlet velocity profile derived from Womersley solution for the upstream tubing. All input uncertainty ranges documented in the UQ input register. Monte Carlo propagation performed across all 13 uncertain inputs simultaneously, yielding aggregate RHI uncertainty of ±9.1%."
    },
