    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out. Uncertainty quantification across 13 input parameters yields RHI uncertainty of ±9.1%, within the acceptance envelope. The screening sensitivity study discussed in the UQ narrative provides qualitative input ranking. Validation against FDA benchmark data demonstrates model fitness for purpose. The RH < 1 criterion is satisfied across all 5 operating points with margin. The credibility evidence package is accepted as sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision.",
